.TH "drm_atomic_set_mode_for_crtc" 9 "drm_atomic_set_mode_for_crtc" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_atomic_set_mode_for_crtc \- set mode for CRTC
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_atomic_set_mode_for_crtc
.BI "(struct drm_crtc_state *state "  ","
.BI "const struct drm_display_mode *mode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "state" 12
the CRTC whose incoming state to update
.IP "mode" 12
kernel-internal mode to use for the CRTC, or NULL to disable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Set a mode (originating from the kernel) on the desired CRTC state and update
the enable property.
.SH "RETURN"
Zero on success, error code on failure. Cannot return -EDEADLK.
